    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i feel like im just stuck in this constant loop. every time i think i finally figured things out, i just end up back at square one. same mistakes, same failures, same heavy feeling in my chest. it's like i'm just wired to fail at everything.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how heavy and frustrating that cycle feels, and it's completely understandable why you'd feel stuck. It's a very common experience to feel like you're running in place, but often what looks like a \"loop\" is actually your brain trying to process a lot of information at once.\n\nThink of it this way: sometimes our minds are just like a small, cluttered room where a few stubborn, mischievous little goblins are hiding in the corners. These goblins aren't trying to stop you from moving forward; they're just so excited about the idea of \"failure\" that they've decided to sit on your shoulders and whisper, \"You can't do it!\" every time you try to solve a problem. They're like tiny, persistent goblins who love to trip you up just to see you squirm.\n\nBut here's the thing: those goblins are just noise. They're not the whole story. Just because you've made the same mistake before doesn't mean you're wired to fail; it just means you haven't yet found the right way to talk back to them. Maybe you need to take a step back, clear out a bit of the room, and realize that the goblins are just",
      "source": "target",
